<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-81-0137 </DOCNO><TEXT>The diagnosis of multiple sclerosis (MS) in patients presenting with signsand symptoms of pure spinal cord involvement is always difficult. Previousstudies have shown the usefulness of encephalic magnetic resonance imaging(MRI) of the brain in those cases. The aim was to evaluate the diagnosisvalue of brain MRI in medullar forms of MS. 3 refs.</TEXT></DOC>